So here's my theory (and I don't know all the names yet so bear with me).
The girl being dragged in the beginning is in a mental institution and is being treated for going against her religion by being gay and falling in love with a girl. The girl she fell in love with is Soyeon who is also in the asylum. Following their story I would say that Soyeon wants to be "set free" or let out because she doesn't feel like their love is wrong. She eventually tries to escape but is trapped by the barbed wire and unable to leave and in the end her lover (black and white hair) commits suicide (gunshot). And the song is her remembering how she got in this situation.

I feel that Myeon is a Goddess watching from the sky to see if Soyeon and her lover will make the choice to ignore sin and the other girl (Soojin the blond?) Is a demon trying to lead them into temptation and supposed sin. While Yuqi is the secret lover of Soojin but their relationship is forbidden but Yuqi doesn't know why she's being forced to endure. The only person I'm confused about is Shuhua I think she is? The one in the big white dress at the end?

snippet.textDisplay:
THEORY: Soojin and Shuhua are the same "being" in a way. The sets for Miyeon, Soojin and Shuhua are all the same, the difference being Miyeon is on top of a higher stage, while Shuhua and Soojin are in the exact same pedestal. Between the both of them, is the difference in atmosphere (a darker vibe for Soojin and a much more heavenly vibe for Shuhua). I think they're the same person since it makes sense. Miyeon says "Insanely beautiful but when I look back again, it's like a devil." I think both Shuhua and Soojin are "temptation" personified, but Shuhua is the one that doesn't seem like it at first (she has the same scene at the barbed wires with Soyeon, which is quite weird if she was portrayed as an angel/a good person).

This other theory might be kind of a reach, but Soyeon and Minnie might be the "lesbian couple" in the MV. Think about it, they're both in the white room, and they're both LITERALLY in hell in the end. For me, Soyeon is the temptress and Minnie is the victim. In the first chorus, Soyeon wears all black (like Soojin) while surrounded by faceless dancers, while Minnie "stays" in the white room, but there are a few dancers there with her. Minnie, the victim, is solemn and empty-looking throughout the video while Soyeon is the opposite.

Also, this is a big thing that I think a lot of people misunderstood, but "Oh my god" is not a shocked exclamation, but more of a prayer for forgiveness for falling into temptation. "Oh, my god, she took me to the sky." All opinion though.

snippet.textDisplay:
THIS CAN BE REALLY LONG. Like REALLY LOOOOOONGG but if you want to know some of my thoughts, feel free to read.


My interpretation for this masterpiece. If you pause at certain parts, you can get what I mean. And the reading of the description may also help.


DESCRIPTION:
Going through “denial,” “confusion,” “acceptance,” and “confidence” and colliding with reality makes you realize that you have to believe in yourself. I trust myself (I trust). I can be confident just by believing in myself.


in the first part you can see Minnie being dragged into a white place (of what seems to be a purgatory or something). The white place is really closed (not much windows or doors). This may represent the denial and the confusion based on the description given on top. Soyeon and Minnie are in a place of denial and confusion and is trying to get out of that place.


Now we can see the red wine multiple times. In the beginning, Minnie was watching the wine being poured into the glass. Now after that part you can see a red liquid in Soyeon's mouth making me think that she drank that wine to see if she can get out of her misery thus the lyrics, "Help me, Help me as if I'm out of breath. I feel" and "Set me free, Set me free as if I'm gonna melt. So Sick." This wine may represent the idea of trust or maybe the truth. They've been trapped into that place of denial and confusion.

When Soyeon drank that, she felt as if she were like a different person. Slowly realizing that it is a reality and that she should

trust herself. She should be confident and that she should believe in herself.


You can see that the white place had a certain exit and Minnie crawling to see what's inside. This leads to Yuqi walking in all white (maybe, she came from the white place too) and looking outside the window (?) I'm not sure though but based on the color, you can see that the light came from the outside where Soojin is. You can also see Soyeon watching her like she was some kind of angel. Maybe Yuqi was walking towards another door or something.


Now from the lyrics, "fall head over heals and you toy with my heart," maybe at first she rejected the wine because she was already confused and lost and all that. So as she goes on she thinks that all will be fine, believing that it is just some kind of trick. So she goes believing into some kind of lie. And then you can see her falling/tripping as if she was being stopped.


And then another door opens leading to Miyeon in all white, looking pretty and shiny. She stands there alone. The lyrics, "Dangerous yet I want to own it and hold on to this pain. Still I let you in" Maybe she represents a person who constantly rejects the truth. She may have rejected the wine multiple times leading her to be on top of what seems to be a small space where she can only have limited moves. This may represent the idea of constantly rejecting the truth and believing into something she thinks is beautiful and right. But in the end it is just making her feel lonely and trapped.


And then we go back to Yuqi is seen being in a state of awe. Maybe the reason is because she saw Soojin or is it because Soojin came to save her from a lie and show her the truth. And then you can see a cup of wine falling from a someone's hand. You may think that it is Yuqi who drank it but, no. That hand had white colored nails. If you pause slowly during Yuqi's part, she had her hands together, showing,red and black colored nails while Miyeon had white. Maybe after Soojin came to save Yuqi, she then came to save Miyeon making her drink the wine.


And then boom! You see Soyeon in all black. A totally different person. She finally realized herself of the truth. She can be confident and free now that she is confident and has trust in herself. So the lyrics, "Oh my God, She took me to the sky. Oh my God she showed me all the stars," may or may not represent Soojin. I mean she came ther to save everyone from their troubles so it may possibly mean that Soojin is the She.


And then we have the gorgeous Soojin who is at the same place where Miyeon was (don't believe me. Pause the parts and look closely). So she may have succesfully saved the girls. She is sitting down, free to move and do anything she wants with other dancers who I believe are some of who she saved.


Then we go to Soyeon's rap. Just read it and you'll understand the meaning. From the part where she said, "Can't stop how could I get away from Her." she once again sees Soojin who acts as an angel. I did research the last part of her rap, "If this is sin, I'll then pay the piper." Piper means bearing the consequence of an action that one has enjoyed. Well that explains her rap though. I won't go further with that because it is kind of easy to understand, I guess.


Then we're back with Miyeon but she's not alone anymore. She's with Soojin's bg dancers. She then goes to explain of what she saw or how she sees Soojin. The lyrics, "Insanely beautiful yet seems like a devil. You make me to let yourself in." And then pushes herself down and falls into a place where we can call hell or a dark place. We can interpret that she has finally realized herself. And then we have Yuqi again but her eyes are different. She now has red stains in her eyes, basically transforming into a different person.


And then we have Shuhua who is also in white with purple background. The lyrics, "I color myself with strong purple scent," can mean many things. In the perspective of those who believe this is a song about being lesbians/gay, Purple can mean that it is a sexually deprived color or a sexual frustration. In the perspective of the Christians, Purple is sometimes used in the Church. So may think that, but if we go deeper into the other historical meaning of purple, it represents loyalty, wisdom, mystery, dignity, and magic. And then you can see Soojin again whispering something to her and her falling from the sky while Soyeon is reaching out to her. Soojin then goes to say, "Ab Imo Pectore," which means "from the bottom of my heart", "with deepest affection", or "sincerely." Now we can go thinking again in the perspective of those who are gay for these girls, that it can be about lesbians/gays. You can believe that since we all have different interpretations for this masterpiece. But if we go deep, It can mean a deep affection for oneself. To love who they are. To be confident. To trust herself. It can mean that too.


And then you see Soyeon covered in red, as if she came back to life. She looks free and wild, though. And then you see all girls who turned into a different person while wearing black and then you see crosses. Well in Christianity the Cross has something to do with Christ. If we relate this song to that it may mean that these girls have resurrected from denial, confusion, or being lost. And then you see Soojin enjoying herself with red petals around her as if she succeeded. Maybe the petals are used for the wine or idk. And then we go back to Minnie who is slowly transforming into something black. She may have drank the wine in the first parts. She then wakes up into the same place where Soyeon was thus ending the song.


Now this song can mean different things. White can mean something as deceiving or a lie. White isn't always as pure as it can be. When you lie, people sometimes believe in those. Because of it being white and thought of as pure, we don't see the lies in it. Something so pretty, shiny and beautiful can be deceiving at first. You may think it's like heaven and good all the time but life isn't always like that. Sometimes you have to get that bad in you to be able to accept yourself. If you're too good all the time you will end up being so naive that you believe in something that is not true to you. But if you go beyond the boundaries, you may be able to see that you are completely yourself. Black may represent that. Black may represent that you go against other people's ideas of you. Black isn't such a bad color. Sometimes people mistake it for that. But the truth is always seen in the baddest of ways. It is seen in the darkest of places. With this you realize, You can be you. You are a lot confident without people telling you who to be. We do have a saying that something so good feels so bad and something so bad feels so good.


Nevertheless, we all have different interpretations to this. This is something I've observed in their mv and lyrics.
